      <ul><li data-original-text=3D"Quantization reduces the precision of m=
odel parameters and activations (for example, from FP32/FP16 to FP8) to shr=
ink memory footprint, improve inference speed, and lower energy consumption=
, while carefully trading off some accuracy; for transformers, this applies=
 to three main elements: weights, activations, and the KV cache in decoder-=
only LLMs.">Quantization reduces the precision of model parameters and acti=
vations (for example, from FP32/FP16 to FP8) to shrink memory footprint, im=
prove inference speed, and lower energy consumption, while carefully tradin=
g off some accuracy; for transformers, this applies to three main elements:=
 weights, activations, and the KV cache in decoder-only LLMs.</li><li data-=
