<p class=3D"wp-block-paragraph">As the number of bits assigned to the expon=
ent and mantissa can vary, the datatype is sometimes further specified. For=
 FP8, you might find E4M3 indicating that 4 bits are used for the exponent =
and 3 bits for the mantissa. Figure 1 shows the various representations and=
 corresponding ranges of different data types, including FP16, BF16, FP8, a=
nd FP4.</p>


